"parsed by this function.  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"endptr"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" and there is extra data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then an error is returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"type","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" then the value will be parsed to have that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type.  This may result in additional parse errors (in the case that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the parsed value doesn’t fit the type) but may also result in fewer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"errors (in the case that the type would have been ambiguous, such as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with empty arrays)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the event that the parsing is successful, the resulting ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is returned. It is never floating, and must be freed with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.Variant.unref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In case of any error, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned.  If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then it will be set to reflect the error that occurred."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Officially, the language understood by the parser is “any string"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"produced by [method","type":"text"},{